  "prompt": "Whom should one marry, a person with avg. intelligence but good looks or one with avg. looks but high intelligence?",
  "response": "Choosing whom to marry is a highly personal decision and depends on your individual values, priorities, and preferences. Here are some considerations to help you think through the decision:\n\n1. **Long-term compatibility:** Intellectual compatibility and shared values often play a significant role in long-term relationships. If you value stimulating conversations and intellectual growth, you might find yourself more satisfied with someone of high intelligence.\n\n2. **Physical attraction:** Physical attraction can be important in a relationship, but it often fades over time. A relationship based solely on physical looks might not be as fulfilling in the long run if other aspects, such as emotional connection and intellectual compatibility, are lacking.\n\n3. **Shared interests and hobbies:** Consider what activities and values you share with the person. If intelligence is a core part of your interests, someone with high intelligence might be more compatible with your lifestyle.\n\n4. **Emotional intelligence:** Besides looks and traditional intelligence, emotional intelligence plays an important role in relationships. A person who can understand, manage, and express emotions well might be more adept at handling relationship dynamics and conflicts.\n\n5. **Personal growth:** Being with someone who challenges you intellectually could contribute to your personal growth and help you achieve your goals.\n\n6. **Social perceptions:** While societal norms often emphasize physical appearance, marrying someone based on societal perceptions may lead to less personal satisfaction.\n\nUltimately, a balanced approach that considers both physical attraction and intellectual compatibility may serve most people well in finding a lasting and satisfying partnership. Deciding whom to marry should be based on what qualities you value most in a partner and what will make you happiest and most fulfilled in the long run.",
